<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,402,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,727,753]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1934" box="[858,1003,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[858,1003,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Hecaloidella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the unique shape of its connective (
<figureCitation box="[247,370,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[222,1372,183,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[211,1377,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia and female pregenital sternite of H. quadripicta species group; A–G, H. brevis; A, aedeagus, lateral view; B, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; C, aedeagus, ventral view; D–E, connective, dorsal and lateral view; F, valve and subgenital plate, dorsal view; G, style; H–L, H. brunnifacialis; H, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; I, aedeagus, caudal view; J, style; K, connective, ventral view; L, female pregenital sternite; M–Q, H. knighti; M, aedeagus, ventral view; N, connective, ventral view; O, style; P, aedeagus and connective, lateral view; Q, female pregenital sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4629116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4629116/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Fig. 7D–E</figureCitation>
